727969f-b.text:
Seagirt Ave., east of Beach 17th Street, showing on the north and south side of Seagirt Ave., the Tackapausha Hotel and the new Hotel Traymore. The last named hotel was known as the Ostend and was operated by David Roach in 1891. This is a set of three views. Views Nos. 2 and 3 show only the last named hotel.

October 1924.
Views 1 & 2.
View 3: May 1923.

727970f-a.text:
Seagirt Ave., north side, between Beach 17th Street and Heyson Road, showing in two views the Tackapausha Hotel located at the N.W. corner of Heyson Road and Seagirt Ave. David Roach was the owner in 1891. The present hotel was erected upon the site of D. Roach's Union Surf Hotel of 1873. Other owners were S. Metzger in 1899, and A. Hartman in 1901.

October 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
